#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.21:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga"
msgstr "3. Persons"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Samiddhasutta"
msgstr "21. Samiddha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.21:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "an3.21:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

#. VAR: samiddho → saviṭṭho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhiko → mahākoṭṭhito (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.21:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca samiddho āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko yenāyasmā sāriputto "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Samiddha and Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita went up to Venerable "
"Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "an3.21:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ samiddhaṃ āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side and Venerable Sāriputta said to Venerable Samiddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.21:2.1"
msgid "“Tayome, āvuso samiddha, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend Samiddha, these three people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an3.21:2.2"
msgid "Katame tayo?"
msgstr "What three?"

#. VAR: diṭṭhippatto → diṭṭhappatto (bj, mr)
msgctxt "an3.21:2.3"
msgid "Kāyasakkhī, diṭṭhippatto, saddhāvimutto."
msgstr ""
"The direct witness, the one attained to view, and the one freed by faith."

msgctxt "an3.21:2.4"
msgid "Ime kho, āvuso, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world."

msgctxt "an3.21:2.5"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ, āvuso, tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ katamo te puggalo khamati abhikkantataro ca "
"paṇītataro cā”ti?"
msgstr "Of these three people, who do you believe to be the finest?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
